h2. Download


h3. Installation

See the "documentation page":admins/admin_documentation.html#installing-the-oar-batch-system for installation requirements and instructions.

h3. Debian packages

You can use the debian repository in your sources.list

bq.  For the 2.2 version:
     deb http://oar.imag.fr/debian_stable_2.2 ./

bq.  For the 2.3 version:
     deb http://oar.imag.fr/debian_stable_2.3 ./

h3. RPM packages

You can use the Yum RPM repository:

Create a /etc/yum.repos.d/oar.repo file containing:

bq.  [oar]
     name=OAR
     baseurl=http://oar.imag.fr/RPMS/stable/2.3
     enabled=1
     gpgcheck=0

